## Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike 4.0 International (CC BY-NC-SA 4.0) - Game Data

The following game data and constants are derived from the Industrialist game and licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0:

### Covered Files:
- `src/data/products.json`
- `src/data/machines.json`
- `src/data/recipes.json`

### Covered Constants (within JavaScript files):
- `src/data/mineshaftDrill.js`:
  - `DRILL_HEADS`, `CONSUMABLES`, `DEPTH_OUTPUTS` arrays
  - All numeric constants (CONSUMABLE_RATES, REPLACEMENT_TIME, POWER_DRILLING, etc.)
  - Deterioration formulas (`getDrillHeadMultiplier`, `getAcidMultiplier`)

- `src/data/logicAssembler.js`:
  - `MICROCHIP_STAGES` array
  - All numeric constants (STEPS_PER_STAGE, AVG_STEP_TIME, POWER_STORAGE_REQUIREMENT, etc.)
  - `BASE_MATERIALS` object

- `src/data/treeFarm.js`:
  - All numeric constants (HARVEST_CYCLE_TIME, LOGS_PER_TREE, HARVESTER_POWER, etc.)
  - `DEFAULT_TREE_FARM_CONFIG` object
  - `getGrowthTime` function (pollution-based growth times)

- `src/data/industrialFirebox.js`:
  - `FUEL_PRODUCTS` array (fuel types and energy values)
  - `RECIPE_ENERGY_REQUIREMENTS` object
  - `RECIPE_ADDITIONAL_WAIT` object

- `src/data/chemicalPlant.js`:
  - Speed/efficiency multiplier formulas (`calculateChemicalPlantMetrics`)
  - `DEFAULT_CHEMICAL_PLANT_SETTINGS` object

- `src/data/undergroundWasteFacility.js`:
  - All numeric constants (STORAGE_CAPACITY, CONCRETE_BLOCKS_PER_FILL, POWER_CONSUMPTION, etc.)
  - Flow scaling formulas

- `src/data/liquidDump.js`:
  - All numeric constants (MAX_FLOW_PER_INPUT, INPUT_COUNT)
  - `WATER_VARIANTS` array
  - Pollution calculation formula (`calculateLiquidDumpPollution`)

- `src/data/liquidBurner.js`:
  - All numeric constants (MAX_FLOW_PER_INPUT, INPUT_COUNT)
  - `WATER_VARIANTS` array
  - Pollution calculation formula (`calculateLiquidBurnerPollution`)

- `src/utils/temperatureUtils.js` (heat source definitions, temperature calculations, temperature-dependent cycle formulas)

### Attribution:
All game data is sourced from the [Industrialist Wiki](https://industrialist.miraheze.org/).

